## Section 2: Alerting Strategy

### 2.1 Severity Tier Definitions

The following table refines and formalises the tiers from ADR-006 and the EDP Monitoring & Alerting Stack spec.

| Tier | Name | Response SLA | Notification Channel | Auto-Page | Examples |
|------|------|-------------|---------------------|-----------|---------|
| P1 | Critical | 15 minutes | PagerDuty (immediate page) + #edp-alerts Slack | Yes | Kafka cluster down, data loss, security breach, consumer lag >10 min on Tier 1 service |
| P2 | High | 1 hour | PagerDuty (low-urgency) + #edp-alerts Slack | Yes (low urgency) | Consumer lag >5 min, DLQ depth >100, Schema Registry down, DB replication lag >30s |
| P3 | Medium | 4 hours (next business day if overnight) | #edp-alerts Slack + Jira ticket auto-created | No | Error rate >1%, disk >80%, cert expiry <14 days, schema compatibility warning |
| P4 | Low | Weekly review
